The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                     NATION BRIEFS
                   
	Kuala Lumpur, Jan. 15 (AFP): Malaysia will ban hotels from hiring foreigners in frontline positions. Victor Wee, secretary general for the tourism ministry, defended the directive saying hotels should not rely on cheap foreign labour.
     
	Airports have already been barred from employing foreign workers. The orders are aimed at reducing migrant labour, an official said today.
         
	New Delhi (PTI): International tour operator Cox amp; Kings has been asked by the Delhi Consumer Commission to pay Rs 8.2 lakh compensation to 10 tourists whose holiday in Europe was turned into a nightmare.
         
	New Delhi (PTI): The CBI today informed the Supreme Court that it had failed to secure an official Spanish-to-English translation of the Argentine court order rejecting its plea for extradition of Bofors accused Ottavio Quattrocchi. The CBI then submitted a copy of the order translated by it. The case will come up again after three weeks.
         
	Nagpur (PTI): The Nagpur rural police have booked a youth on the charge of burgling his father-in-laws house in Kharda village near here. Krishna Dault Khandai broke into the house of Ratiram Kularkar with his cousin Arun on December 27 after removing the roof tiles.
         
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has sought an explanation from the All India Institute of Medical Sciences for allegedly denying treatment to a cancer patient early this month. The hospital had forcibly discharged the patient on February 2 stating he did not require the treatment. 
         
	Kannur (PTI): A week-old boy was found abandoned on a passenger train on Tuesday, railway sources said. The infant, wrapped in a cloth, was found lying in the ladies compartment of the Kozhikode-Kannur train here, they said. The baby was taken to the district hospital.
                                                            
